    "content": "**On the 范畴 / category theory TN question:**\n\nYes, include a brief translator's note at the first occurrence. The risk of confusion is real and specific -- a philosophically literate reader encountering \"category theory\" in a Kantian-saturated text will reasonably wonder which sense is meant. The deliberate overlap makes disambiguation *more* necessary, not less.\n\n**Suggested TN (footnote at first occurrence of 范畴论):**\n\n> **TN:** \"Category theory\" (范畴论) here refers to the mathematical discipline (Eilenberg-Mac Lane), not to Kant's table of categories (*Kategorien*), though the author's use of the term is alive to both senses.\n\nThis is not patronizing -- the confusion is domain-specific (math vs. Continental philosophy), not a matter of reader intelligence. One sentence, first occurrence only, then let the glossary entry do the rest. If the dictionary already covers 范畴/范畴论, a cross-reference (\"see Glossary\") can replace a longer note."
  }
